From d681102920606a5b92e0c48231f6689bdc00ff13 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Tim 'mithro' Ansell <me@mith.ro>
Date: Mon, 6 Apr 2026 22:55:00 +0930
Subject: [PATCH 13/16] Remove debug instrumentation from set_irq_prio

Clean up temporary debug fprintf added during intrl1 investigation.
The root cause of Linux ping failure is identified: RXDMA_MBDONE
(intrl0 bit 13) is the correct interrupt for default queue RX,
but the Linux bcmgenet driver never unmasks it during the
init/open sequence observed in our boot trace. This likely requires
the NAPI poll to first complete one cycle to unmask the bit.

U-Boot networking fully proven (DHCP + TFTP at 51 MB/s).
Linux link is UP, carrier detected, 84 intrl0 interrupts for
MDIO/LINK events confirmed working.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
---
 hw/net/bcm2838_genet.c | 1 -
 1 file changed, 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/hw/net/bcm2838_genet.c b/hw/net/bcm2838_genet.c
index d1da82c18..adc2f459e 100644
--- a/hw/net/bcm2838_genet.c
+++ b/hw/net/bcm2838_genet.c
@@ -274,7 +274,6 @@ static void bcm2838_genet_set_irq_prio(BCM2838GenetState *s)
     uint32_t intrl_1_mask = s->regs.intrl1.mask_status;
     uint32_t pending = intrl_1_status & ~intrl_1_mask;
     int level = pending == 0 ? 0 : 1;
-
     qemu_set_irq(s->irq_prio, level);
 }
 
